            <title>[FLINK-4038] Impossible to set more than 1 JVM argument in env.java.opts</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-4038</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The Taskmanager start scripts fail when env.java.opts contains more than 1 jvm opts due to:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if [[ $FLINK_TM_MEM_PRE_ALLOCATE == &quot;false&quot; ]] &amp;amp;&amp;amp; [ -z $FLINK_ENV_JAVA_OPTS ]; then&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;-z checks the length of the first argument but it fails if it has more than 1 argument&lt;/p&gt;</description>
